  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat and brown the speck until crisp.",
    "Remove speck, add minced beef to the skillet, cooking until browned.",
    "Add chopped onion and carrot, sauté until softened.",
    "Stir in tomato paste and cook for 1 minute until fragrant.",
    "Deglaze the pan with red wine, scraping up browned bits, and let the wine reduce by half.",
    "Pour in beef stock, add thyme and rosemary, bring to a simmer and cook for 15 minutes.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a baking dish and top with cauliflower mash.",
    "Scatter bacon bits over the mash and dot with butter.",
    "Bake in a preheated oven at 200°C for 20 minutes until the top is golden.",
    "Let rest 5 minutes before serving."
